      "comment": "GOLDEN LABEL (1) flew the lids from out wide with an impressive turn of foot before finishing second (19.75) and beaten 2.75 lengths over 352m at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Rates highly and will give a great sight. REDBACK JACK (2) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing third behind Sutton's Magic (22.00) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Must be included in calculations. CHAMPAGNE FIZZ (8) produced a modest effort most recently when seventh at this track over 352m behind Hayden's Gift (20.26) in a Grade 5. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. INSANE DANCER (7) placed last time and cannot be ignored.",
